ame\": \"GitHub Copilot\",\n    71→    \"title\": \"Visual Studio Code v1.110 February Release\",\n    72→    \"description\": \"GitHub Copilot released enhanced agent capabilities for longer-running and complex tasks, improved control over agent workflows, and security updates in version 1.110.1 addressing issues in core and the GitHub Copilot Chat extension.\",\n    73→    \"updateType\": \"release\",\n    74→    \"url\": \"https://github.blog/changelog/2026-03-06-github-copilot-in-visual-studio-code-v1-110-february-release/\",\n    75→    \"date\": \"2026-03-06\",\n    76→    \"community_feedback\": [\n    77→      {\n    78→        \"quote\": \"Since we're talking about GitHub Copilot I'll lodge my biggest complaint about it here! The context window is stuck at 128k for all models\",\n    79→        \"source\": \"HN\",\n    80→        \"sentiment\": \"negative\"\n    81→      },\n    82→      {\n    83→        \"quote\": \"The Visual Studio Code February 2026 release makes agents practical for longer-running and more complex tasks\",\n    84→        \"source\": \"GitHub Blog\",\n    85→        \"sentiment\": \"positive\"\n    86→      }\n    87→    ]\n    88→  },\n    89→  {\n    90→    \"productName\": \"Codex CLI\",\n    91→    \"title\": \"Version 0.114.0 - Experimental Code Mode\",\n    92→    \"description\": \"Codex CLI 0.114.0 released with an experimental code mode for more isolated coding workflows and an experimental hooks engine with SessionStart and Stop functionality.\",\n    93→    \"updateType\": \"release\",\n    94→    \"url\": \"https://developers.openai.com/codex/changelog/\",\n    95→    \"date\": \"2026-03-11\",\n    96→    \"community_feedback\": []\n    97→  },\n    98→  {\n    99→    \"productName\": \"Codex CLI\",\n   100→    \"title\": \"Version 0.110.0 - Plugin System\",\n   101→    \"description\": \"Codex CLI 0.110.0 introduced a plugin system to load skills and MCP entries, along with improvements to the multi-agent Terminal User Interface (TUI).\",\n   102→    \"updateType\": \"feature\",\n   103→    \"url\": \"https://developers.openai.com/codex/changelog/\",\n   104→    \"date\": \"2026-03-05\",\n   105→    \"community_feedback\": []\n   106→  },\n   107→  {\n   108→    \"productName\": \"Gemini CLI\",\n   109→    \"title\": \"v0.32.0 - Generalist Agent & Model Steering\",\n   110→    \"description\": \"Gemini CLI v0.32.0 released with the generalist agent now enabled to improve task delegation and routing, and new model steering capabilities within workspace environments. Patch release v0.32.1 followed with cherry-picked fixes.\",\n   111→    \"updateType\": \"release\",\n   112→    \"url\": \"https://geminicli.com/docs/changelogs/\",\n   113→    \"date\": \"2026-03-03\",\n   114→    \"community_feedback\": []\n   115→  },\n   116→  {\n   117→    \"productName\": \"Devin\",\n   118→    \"title\": \"Install Devin as an App (PWA)\",\n   119→    \"description\": \"Devin can now be installed as a Progressive Web App (PWA) on both desktop and mobile devices. Users can install by opening app.devin.ai in Chrome or Edge and clicking the install icon in the address bar. Release includes minor bug fixes, performance improvements, and visual polish.\",\n   120→    \"updateType\": \"feature\",\n   121→    \"url\": \"https://docs.devin.ai/release-notes/overview\",\n   122→    \"date\": \"2026-03-07\",\n   123→    \"community_feedback\": [\n   124→      {\n   125→        \"quote\": \"Where did Devin go? What does it say about the future of AI dev tools?\",\n   126→        \"source\": \"Reddit\",\n   127→        \"sentiment\": \"neutral\"\n   128→      }\n   129→    ]\n   130→  }\n   131→]\n   132→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"
