→            body {\n   257→                background-color: #ffffff;\n   258→            }\n   259→\n   260→            section {\n   261→                break-inside: avoid;\n   262→                border: 1px solid #000000;\n   263→            }\n   264→\n   265→            a {\n   266→                color: #000000;\n   267→                text-decoration: underline;\n   268→            }\n   269→        }\n   270→\n   271→        /* Hover effects */\n   272→        .item:hover {\n   273→            background-color: #fafafa;\n   274→        }\n   275→\n   276→        .item-title a:hover {\n   277→            color: #ff6600;\n   278→        }\n   279→    </style>\n   280→</head>\n   281→<body>\n   282→    <header>\n   283→        <div class=\"container\">\n   284→            <div class=\"logo\">\n   285→                <a href=\"#\">Agentic Coding Daily</a>\n   286→            </div>\n   287→            <div class=\"nav-links\">\n   288→                <a href=\"#\">new</a> |\n   289→                <a href=\"#\">past</a> |\n   290→                <a href=\"#\">comments</a> |\n   291→                <a href=\"#\">ask</a> |\n   292→                <a href=\"#\">show</a> |\n   293→                <a href=\"#\">jobs</a> |\n   294→                <a href=\"#\">submit</a>\n   295→            </div>\n   296→        </div>\n   297→    </header>\n   298→\n   299→    <div class=\"sub-header\">\n   300→        <div class=\"container\">\n   301→            <span class=\"date-badge\">2026-03-13</span>\n   302→            <span style=\"margin-left: 10px; color: #000000;\">Daily research report on agentic coding tools and AI development</span>\n   303→        </div>\n   304→    </div>\n   305→\n   306→    <main>\n   307→        <div class=\"container\">\n   308→            <div class=\"three-column-layout\">\n   309→                <!-- New Products Section -->\n   310→                <section class=\"new-products\">\n   311→                    <h2>New Products (9)</h2>\n   312→\n   313→                    <div class=\"item\">\n   314→                        <div class=\"item-title\"><a href=\"https://www.producthunt.com/products/insforge-alpha\" target=\"_blank\">InsForge</a></div>\n   315→                        <div class=\"item-description\">Backend platform built for AI agents to build and ship fullstack applications. Provides authentication, database, storage, functions, and AI integrations. Open source with 2.3K+ GitHub stars.</div>\n   316→                        <div class=\"item-meta\">\n   317→                            <span class=\"tag\">code agent</span>\n   318→                            <span class=\"source-badge\">Product Hunt</span>\n   319→                            <span class=\"tag\">2026-03-11</span>\n   320→                        </div>\n   321→                        <div class=\"quote\">\"Turn your coding agent into full-stack engineer\"</div>\n   322→                    </div>\n   323→\n   324→                    <div class=\"item\">\n   325→                        <div class=\"item-title\"><a href=\"https://www.producthunt.com/products/extract-by-firecrawl\" target=\"_blank\">Firecrawl CLI</a></div>\n   326→                        <div class=\"item-description\">All-in-one CLI toolkit for scraping, searching, and browsing the web, specifically built for AI agents and developers. Provides clean, reliable data with a Browser Sandbox feature.</div>\n   327→                        <div class=\"item-meta\">\n   328→                            <span class=\"tag\">AI coding CLI</span>\n   329→                            <span class=\"source-badge\">Product Hunt</span>\n   330→                            <span class=\"tag\">2026-03-11</span>\n   331→                        </div>\n   332→                        <div class=\"quote\">\"The complete web data toolkit for AI agents\"</div>\n   333→                    </div>\n   334→\n   335→                    <div class=\"item\">\n   336→                        <div class=\"item-title\"><a href=\"https://www.producthunt.com/products/codeyam-cli-memory\" target=\"_blank\">CodeYam CLI & Memory</a></div>\n   337→                        <div class=\"item-description\">Comprehensive memory management for Claude Code. Uses a background agent to review coding session transcripts, identifies confusion patterns, and generates targeted rules to improve coding efficiency.</div>\n   338→                        <div class=\"item-meta\">\n   339→                            <span class=\"tag\">AI coding CLI</span>\n   340→                            <span class=\"source-badge\">Product Hunt, HN</span>\n   341→                            <span class=\"tag\">2026-03-11</span>\n   342→                        </div>\n   343→                        <div class=\"quote\">\"Claude Code kept repeating the same mistakes - this tool solves that\"</div>\n   344→                    </div>\n   345→\n   346→                    <div class=\"item\">\n   347→                        <div class=\"item-title\"><a href=\"https://www.producthunt.com\" target=\"_blank\">Spine Swarm</a></div>\n   348→                        <div class=\"item-description\">Manages a team of AI agents that do real work together. Coordinates multiple AI coding agents for complex tasks.</div>\n   349→                        <div class=\"item-meta\">\n   350→                            <span class=\"tag\">code agent</span>\n   351→                            <span class=\"source-badge\">Product Hunt</span>\n   352→                            <span class=\"tag\">2026-03-10</span>\n   353→                        </div>\n   354→                    </div>\n   355→\n   356→                    <div class=\"item\">\n   357→                        <div class=\"item-title\"><a href=\"https://www.producthunt.com\" target=\"_blank\">Unblocked</a></div>\n   358→                        <div class=\"item-description\">Gets AI agents to generate code that fits your system architecture and constraints.</div>\n   359→                        <div class=\"item-meta\">\n   360→                            <span class=\"tag\">code agent</span>\n   361→                            <span class=\"source-badge\">Product Hunt</span>\n   362→                            <span class=\"tag\">2026-03-10</span>\n   363→                        </div>\n   364→                    </div>\n   365→\n   366→                    <div class=\"item\">\n   367→                        <div class=\"item-title\"><a href=\"https://www.producthunt.com\" target=\"_blank\">Agent Skills</a></div>\n   368→                        <div class=\"item-description\">Finds and integrates skills for Claude Code, Cursor, Copilot and other AI coding tools. Part of the emerging Agent Skills open standard that allows AI coding assistants to perform agentic tasks.</div>\n   369→                        <div class=\"item-meta\">\n   370→                            <span class=\"tag\">AI coding CLI</span>\n   371→                            <span class=\"source-badge\">Product Hunt</span>\n   372→                            <span class=\"tag\">2026-03-10</span>\n   373→                        </div>\n   374→                        <div class=\"quote\">\"Agent skills follow an open standard across Claude Code, Cursor, and Copilot\"</div>\n   375→                    </div>\n   376→\n   377→                    <div class=\"item\">\n   378→                        <div class=\"item-title\"><a href=\"https://www.producthunt.com\" target=\"_blank\">Claude Marketplace</a></div>\n   379→                        <div class=\"item-description\">Helps companies easily discover and acquire the AI tools they need for development workflows. Streamlines procurement of AI development tools.</div>\n   380→                        <div class=\"item-meta\">\n   381→                            <span class=\"tag\">workflow agent</span>\n   382→                            <span class=\"source-badge\">Product Hunt</span>\n   383→                            <span class=\"tag\">2026-03-08</span>\n   384→                        </div>\n   385→                    </div>\n   386→\n   387→                    <div class=\"item\">\n   388→                        <div class=\"item-title\"><a href=\"https://www.producthunt.com\" target=\"_blank\">Superset</a></div>\n   389→                        <div class=\"item-description\">Runs an army of Claude Code, Codex, and other AI coding agents on your machine simultaneously. Enables parallel execution of multiple AI coding agents.</div>\n   390→                        <div class=\"item-meta\">\n   391→                            <span class=\"tag\">AI coding CLI</span>\n   392→                            <span class=\"source-badge\">Product Hunt</span>\n   393→                            <span class=\"tag\">2026-02-27</span>\n   394→                        </div>\n   395→                    </div>\n   396→\n   397→                    <div class=\"item\">\n   398→                        <div class=\"item-title\"><a href=\"https://www.producthunt.com\" target=\"_blank\">memories.sh</a></div>\n   399→                        <div class=\"item-description\">One layer for memories, skills, and rules across any AI agent. Provides unified memory management for multiple AI coding agents, addressing the challenge of context persistence across sessions.</div>\n   400→                        <div class=\"item-meta\">\n   401→                            <span class=\"tag\">AI coding CLI</span>\n   402→                            <span class=\"source-badge\">Product Hunt</span>\n   403→                            <span class=\"tag\">2026-02-27</span>\n   404→                        </div>\n   405→                    </div>\n   406→                </section>\n   407→\n   408→                <!-- Whitelist Updates Section -->\n   409→                <section class=\"whitelist-updates\">\n   410→                    <h2>Whitelist Updates (7)</h2>\n   411→\n   412→                    <div class=\"item\">\n   413→                        <div class=\"item-title\">\n   414→                            <a href=\"https://releasebot.io/updates/anthropic/claude\" target=\"_blank\">Claude Code</a>\n   415→                            <span class=\"version-badge\">Auto Mode</span>\n   416→                        </div>\n   417→                        <div class=\"item-description\">Launched new 'Auto Mode' feature. Claude Code access was added to Team plan Standard seats, expanding availability to enterprise team users.</div>\n   418→                        <div class=\"item-meta\">\n   419→                            <span class=\"update-type\">feature</span>\n   420→                            <span class=\"source-badge\">2026-03-12</span>\n   421→                        </div>\n   422→                        <div class=\"quote\">\"Anthropic announced a research preview feature called Auto Mode for Claude Code\"</div>\n   423→                    </div>\n   424→\n   425→                    <div class=\"item\">\n   426→                        <div class=\"item-title\">\n   427→                            <a href=\"https://windsurf.com/changelog\" target=\"_blank\">Windsurf</a>\n   428→                            <span class=\"version-badge\">v1.9577.24</span>\n   429→                        </div>\n   430→                        <div class=\"item-description\">Released GPT-5.4 with limited-time promotional pricing. New reasoning tiers (No Reasoning at 1x credits through Extra High Reasoning at 8x credits), bug fixes for Jupyter Notebook performance, Cascade UI rendering improvements.</div>\n   431→                        <div class=\"item-meta\">\n   432→                            <span class=\"update-type\">release</span>\n   433→                            <span class=\"source-badge\">2026-03-09</span>\n   434→                        </div>\n   435→                        <div class=\"quote\">\"GPT-5.4's deeper exploration and higher attention to detail compared to other tested models\"</div>\n   436→                    </div>\n   437→\n   438→                    <div class=\"item\">\n   439→                        <div class=\"item-title\">\n   440→                            <a href=\"https://github.blog/changelog/2026-03-06-github-copilot-in-visual-studio-code-v1-110-february-release/\" target=\"_blank\">GitHub Copilot</a>\n   441→                            <span class=\"version-badge\">v1.110</span>\n   442→                        </div>\n   443→                        <div class=\"item-description\">Enhanced agent capabilities for longer-running and complex tasks, improved control over agent workflows, and security updates addressing issues in core and the GitHub Copilot Chat extension.</div>\n   444→                        <div class=\"item-meta\">\n   445→                            <span class=\"update-type\">release</span>\n   446→                            <span class=\"source-badge\">2026-03-06</span>\n   447→                        </div>\n   448→                        <div class=\"quote\">\"Makes agents practical for longer-running and more complex tasks\"</div>\n   449→                    </div>\n   450→\n   451→                    <div class=\"item\">\n   452→                        <div class=\"item-title\">\n   453→                            <a href=\"https://developers.openai.com/codex/changelog/\" target=\"_blank\">Codex CLI</a>\n   454→                            <span class=\"version-badge\">v0.107.0</span>\n   455→                        </div>\n   456→                        <div class=\"item-description\">Improved approval prompts and app connection sign-in flows, along with additional performance improvements and bug fixes.</div>\n   457→                        <div class=\"item-meta\">\n   458→                            <span class=\"update-type\">release</span>\n   459→                            <span class=\"source-badge\">2026-03-02</span>\n   460→                        </div>\n   461→                    </div>\n   462→\n   463→                    <div class=\"item\">\n   464→                        <div class=\"item-title\">\n   465→                            <a href=\"https://developers.openai.com/codex/changelog/\" target=\"_blank\">Codex CLI</a>\n   466→                            <span class=\"version-badge\">v0.106.0</span>\n   467→                        </div>\n   468→                        <div class=\"item-description\">Added a direct install script for macOS, simplifying the installation process for Mac users.</div>\n   469→                        <div class=\"item-meta\">\n   470→                            <span class=\"update-type\">feature</span>\n   471→                            <span class=\"source-badge\">2026-02-26</span>\n   472→                        </div>\n   473→                    </div>\n   474→\n   475→                    <div class=\"item\">\n   476→                        <div class=\"item-title\">\n   477→                            <a href=\"https://docs.devin.ai/api-reference/release-notes\" target=\"_blank\">Devin</a>\n   478→                            <span class=\"version-badge\">v3 API</span>\n   479→                        </div>\n   480→                        <div class=\"item-description\">v3 API came out of beta and is now the primary API for all Devin functionality, providing role-based access control, session attribution, and new capabilities.</div>\n   481→                        <div class=\"item-meta\">\n   482→                            <span class=\"update-type\">release</span>\n   483→                            <span class=\"source-badge\">2026-02-27</span>\n   484→                        </div>\n   485→                        <div class=\"quote\">\"Devin 2.2 update from Cognition with Desktop support\"</div>\n   486→                    </div>\n   487→\n   488→                    <div class=\"item\">\n   489→                        <div class=\"item-title\">\n   490→                            <a href=\"https://windsurf.com/changelog\" target=\"_blank\">Windsurf</a>\n   491→                            <span class=\"version-badge\">Feature</span>\n   492→                        </div>\n   493→                        <div class=\"item-description\">New model picker that groups models by family with hovercards showing specific variants. Added POST_CASCADE_RESPONSE_WITH_TRANSCRIPT hook, Cascade hooks configuration visibility, and Linux ARM64 support.</div>\n   494→                        <div class=\"item-meta\">\n   495→                            <span class=\"update-type\">feature</span>\n   496→                            <span class=\"source-badge\">2026-02-25</span>\n   497→                        </div>\n   498→                    </div>\n   499→                </section>\n   500→\n   501→                <!-- Technical Insights Section -->\n   502→                <section class=\"technical-insights\">\n   503→                    <h2>Technical Insights (4)</h2>\n   504→\n   505→                    <div class=\"item\">\n   506→                        <div class=\"item-title\"><a href=\"https://www.forbes.com/sites/richardnieva/2026/03/11/meet-the-9-billion-ai-company-reimagining-vibe-coding-replit-amjad-masad/\" target=\"_blank\">Meet The $9 Billion AI Company Reimagining Vibe Coding</a></div>\n   507→                        <div class=\"item-description\">Forbes profile of Replit CEO Amjad Masad and Agent 4 launch. Replit raised $400M at $9B valuation. Agent 4 introduces digital canvas for vibe coding. Competes with Claude Code ($2.5B revenue) and Cursor ($2B+ revenue).</div>\n   508→                        <div class=\"insight-author\">Richard Nieva, Forbes</div>\n   509→                        <div class=\"insight-topics\">\n   510→                            <span class=\"tag\">vibe coding</span>\n   511→                            <span class=\"tag\">Replit</span>\n   512→                            <span class=\"tag\">funding</span>\n   513→                        </div>\n   514→                        <div class=\"item-meta\" style=\"margin-top: 5px;\">\n   515→                            <span class=\"source-badge\">2026-03-11</span>\n   516→                        </div>\n   517→                    </div>\n   518→\n   519→                    <div class=\"item\">\n   520→                        <div class=\"item-title\"><a href=\"https://simonwillison.net/2026/Mar/9/not-so-boring/\" target=\"_blank\">Perhaps not Boring Technology after all</a></div>\n   521→                        <div class=\"item-description\">Explores concerns that LLMs for programming would push technology choices towards tools best represented in training data. However, with latest models in good coding agent harnesses, finds excellent results even with brand new or private tools.</div>\n   522→                        <div class=\"insight-author\">Simon Willison</div>\n   523→                        <div class=\"insight-topics\">\n   524→                            <span class=\"tag\">LLM</span>\n   525→                            <span class=\"tag\">coding agents</span>\n   526→                            <span class=\"tag\">skills</span>\n   527→                        </div>\n   528→                        <div class=\"item-meta\" style=\"margin-top: 5px;\">\n   529→                            <span class=\"source-badge\">2026-03-09</span>\n   530→                        </div>\n   531→                    </div>\n   532→\n   533→                    <div class=\"item\">\n   534→                        <div class=\"item-title\"><a href=\"https://simonwillison.net/2026/Mar/10/\" target=\"_blank\">AI should help us produce better code</a></div>\n   535→                        <div class=\"item-description\">Addresses concerns that outsourcing code to AI tools will result in quality drops. Argues that shipping worse code with agents is a choice - we can choose to ship better code instead.</div>\n   536→                        <div class=\"insight-author\">Simon Willison</div>\n   537→                        <div class=\"insight-topics\">\n   538→                            <span class=\"tag\">AI</span>\n   539→                            <span class=\"tag\">code quality</span>\n   540→                            <span class=\"tag\">opinion</span>\n   541→                        </div>\n   542→                        <div class=\"item-meta\" style=\"margin-top: 5px;\">\n   543→                            <span class=\"source-badge\">2026-03-10</span>\n   544→                        </div>\n   545→                    </div>\n   546→\n   547→                    <div class=\"item\">\n   548→                        <div class=\"item-title\"><a href=\"https://simonwillison.net/2026/Mar/5/\" target=\"_blank\">Can coding agents relicense open source through a 'clean room' implementation?</a></div>\n   549→                        <div class=\"item-description\">Discusses how coding agents are extraordinarily good at building 'clean room' implementations of code. Also covers GPT-5.4 and GPT-5.4-pro announcement with August 2025 knowledge cutoff, 1M token context.</div>\n   550→                        <div class=\"insight-author\">Simon Willison</div>\n   551→                        <div class=\"insight-topics\">\n   552→                            <span class=\"tag\">licensing</span>\n   553→                            <span class=\"tag\">GPT-5.4</span>\n   554→                            <span class=\"tag\">clean room</span>\n   555→                        </div>\n   556→                        <div class=\"item-meta\" style=\"margin-top: 5px;\">\n   557→                            <span class=\"source-badge\">2026-03-05</span>\n   558→                        </div>\n   559→                    </div>\n   560→                </section>\n   561→            </div>\n   562→        </div>\n   563→    </main>\n   564→\n   565→    <footer>\n   566→        <div class=\"container\">\n   567→            <a href=\"#\">Guidelines</a> |\n   568→            <a href=\"#\">FAQ</a> |\n   569→            <a href=\"#\">Lists</a> |\n   570→            <a href=\"#\">API</a> |\n   571→            <a href=\"#\">Security</a> |\n   572→            <a href=\"#\">Legal</a> |\n   573→            <a href=\"#\">Apply to YC</a> |\n   574→            <a href=\"#\">Contact</a>\n   575→            <div style=\"margin-top: 10px;\">\n   576→                Generated with <a href=\"#\">Claude Code</a> | Agentic Coding Research Report\n   577→            </div>\n   578→        </div>\n   579→    </footer>\n   580→</body>\n   581→</html>\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"
      }
    ]
