class=\"item-description\">Manages teams of AI agents that work together. Coordinates multiple coding agents for complex tasks including web browsing. Visual workspace for deploying swarms. <span class=\"highlight\">163 upvotes</span></div>\n   362→                    <div class=\"item-meta\">\n   363→                        <span class=\"tag\">code agent</span>\n   364→                        <span class=\"tag\">Product Hunt</span>\n   365→                    </div>\n   366→                    <div class=\"quote\">\"Manage and deploy swarms of AI agents\"</div>\n   367→                </div>\n   368→\n   369→                <div class=\"item\">\n   370→                    <div class=\"item-title\"><a href=\"https://www.producthunt.com\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Claude Code Review</a></div>\n   371→                    <div class=\"item-description\">Multi-agent review system that catches bugs early in AI-generated code. <span class=\"highlight\">467 upvotes</span> - strong community validation for automated code review.</div>\n   372→                    <div class=\"item-meta\">\n   373→                        <span class=\"tag\">workflow agent</span>\n   374→                        <span class=\"tag\">Product Hunt</span>\n   375→                    </div>\n   376→                    <div class=\"quote\">\"Multi-agent review catching bugs early\"</div>\n   377→                </div>\n   378→\n   379→                <div class=\"item\">\n   380→                    <div class=\"item-title\"><a href=\"https://www.producthunt.com\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Unblocked</a></div>\n   381→                    <div class=\"item-description\">Gets AI agents to generate code fitting your system architecture. Context layer for AI-driven development. Surfaces context from repos, Slack, Jira, docs, PR history.</div>\n   382→                    <div class=\"item-meta\">\n   383→                        <span class=\"tag\">code agent</span>\n   384→                        <span class=\"tag\">Product Hunt</span>\n   385→                    </div>\n   386→                    <div class=\"quote\">\"The context layer for AI-driven development\"</div>\n   387→                </div>\n   388→\n   389→                <div class=\"item\">\n   390→                    <div class=\"item-title\"><a href=\"https://www.producthunt.com\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Agent Skills</a></div>\n   391→                    <div class=\"item-description\">Finds and integrates skills for Claude Code, Cursor, Copilot. Part of Agent Skills open standard allowing AI assistants to perform agentic tasks.</div>\n   392→                    <div class=\"item-meta\">\n   393→                        <span class=\"tag\">AI coding CLI</span>\n   394→                        <span class=\"tag\">open standard</span>\n   395→                        <span class=\"tag\">Product Hunt</span>\n   396→                    </div>\n   397→                </div>\n   398→\n   399→                <div class=\"item\">\n   400→                    <div class=\"item-title\"><a href=\"https://www.producthunt.com/products/pulldog\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Pulldog</a></div>\n   401→                    <div class=\"item-description\">Native macOS app for organizing code reviews from GitHub and GitLab. Single place to monitor reviews with smart queries. Aggregates multiple accounts.</div>\n   402→                    <div class=\"item-meta\">\n   403→                        <span class=\"tag\">workflow agent</span>\n   404→                        <span class=\"tag\">macOS</span>\n   405→                        <span class=\"tag\">Product Hunt</span>\n   406→                    </div>\n   407→                    <div class=\"quote\">\"A Mac app to keep your code reviews organized\"</div>\n   408→                </div>\n   409→\n   410→                <div class=\"item\">\n   411→                    <div class=\"item-title\"><a href=\"https://www.producthunt.com\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Claude Marketplace</a></div>\n   412→                    <div class=\"item-description\">Helps companies discover and acquire AI tools for development workflows. Streamlines procurement of AI development tools.</div>\n   413→                    <div class=\"item-meta\">\n   414→                        <span class=\"tag\">workflow agent</span>\n   415→                        <span class=\"tag\">Product Hunt</span>\n   416→                    </div>\n   417→                </div>\n   418→\n   419→                <div class=\"item\">\n   420→                    <div class=\"item-title\"><a href=\"https://www.producthunt.com\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Clean Clode</a></div>\n   421→                    <div class=\"item-description\">Instantly cleans Claude Code and Codex terminal output. Improves readability of AI coding agent output in terminal.</div>\n   422→                    <div class=\"item-meta\">\n   423→                        <span class=\"tag\">AI coding CLI</span>\n   424→                        <span class=\"tag\">Product Hunt</span>\n   425→                    </div>\n   426→                </div>\n   427→\n   428→                <div class=\"item\">\n   429→                    <div class=\"item-title\"><a href=\"https://www.producthunt.com\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Aura</a></div>\n   430→                    <div class=\"item-description\">Semantic version control for AI coding agents on top of Git. Provides versioning and tracking for AI-generated code changes.</div>\n   431→                    <div class=\"item-meta\">\n   432→                        <span class=\"tag\">workflow agent</span>\n   433→                        <span class=\"tag\">Product Hunt</span>\n   434→                    </div>\n   435→                </div>\n   436→\n   437→                <div class=\"item\">\n   438→                    <div class=\"item-title\"><a href=\"https://www.producthunt.com\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">CtrlAI</a></div>\n   439→                    <div class=\"item-description\">Transparent proxy that secures AI agents with guardrails. Provides security and governance for AI coding agents in production environments.</div>\n   440→                    <div class=\"item-meta\">\n   441→                        <span class=\"tag\">workflow orchestration</span>\n   442→                        <span class=\"tag\">security</span>\n   443→                        <span class=\"tag\">Product Hunt</span>\n   444→                    </div>\n   445→                </div>\n   446→            </section>\n   447→\n   448→            <!-- Whitelist Updates Section -->\n   449→            <section id=\"whitelist-updates\">\n   450→                <h2>Product Updates (10)</h2>\n   451→\n   452→                <div class=\"update-item\">\n   453→                    <div class=\"update-product\">Cursor</div>\n   454→                    <div class=\"update-title\">New Plugins on Cursor Marketplace</div>\n   455→                    <div class=\"update-description\">Added 30+ new plugins from Atlassian, Datadog, GitLab, Glean, Hugging Face, monday.com, PlanetScale. Plugins contain MCPs for cloud agents.</div>\n   456→                    <div class=\"update-date\">2026-03-11</div>\n   457→                    <div class=\"update-link\"><a href=\"https://cursor.com/changelog\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">View Changelog →</a></div>\n   458→                </div>\n   459→\n   460→                <div class=\"update-item\">\n   461→                    <div class=\"update-product\">GitHub Copilot</div>\n   462→                    <div class=\"update-title\">Major Agentic Capabilities in JetBrains IDEs</div>\n   463→                    <div class=\"update-description\">v1.6.1 with enhanced core agentic capabilities, custom agent features, and quality-of-life improvements.</div>\n   464→                    <div class=\"update-date\">2026-03-11</div>\n   465→                    <div class=\"update-link\"><a href=\"https://github.blog/changelog/2026-03-11-major-agentic-capabilities-improvements-in-github-copilot-for-jetbrains-ides/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">View Changelog →</a></div>\n   466→                </div>\n   467→\n   468→                <div class=\"update-item\">\n   469→                    <div class=\"update-product\">Codex CLI</div>\n   470→                    <div class=\"update-title\">Version 0.114.0 - Experimental Code Mode</div>\n   471→                    <div class=\"update-description\">Experimental code mode for isolated coding workflows and experimental hooks engine with SessionStart/Stop functionality.</div>\n   472→                    <div class=\"update-date\">2026-03-11</div>\n   473→                    <div class=\"update-link\"><a href=\"https://developers.openai.com/codex/changelog/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">View Changelog →</a></div>\n   474→                </div>\n   475→\n   476→                <div class=\"update-item\">\n   477→                    <div class=\"update-product\">GitHub Copilot</div>\n   478→                    <div class=\"update-title\">GPT-5.4 Generally Available</div>\n   479→                    <div class=\"update-description\">GPT-5.4 now available for Pro, Business, Enterprise. Early testing shows high success rates in agentic software development.</div>\n   480→                    <div class=\"update-date\">2026-03-05</div>\n   481→                    <div class=\"update-link\"><a href=\"https://github.blog/changelog/2026-03-05-gpt-5-4-is-generally-available-in-github-copilot/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">View Changelog →</a></div>\n   482→                    <div class=\"quote\">\"Consistently hits high rates of success\"</div>\n   483→                    <div class=\"quote\">\"Is GPT-5.4 telling too many jokes?\"</div>\n   484→                </div>\n   485→\n   486→                <div class=\"update-item\">\n   487→                    <div class=\"update-product\">GitHub Copilot</div>\n   488→                    <div class=\"update-title\">VS Code v1.110 February Release</div>\n   489→                    <div class=\"update-description\">Enhanced agent capabilities for longer-running complex tasks, improved workflow control, security updates.</div>\n   490→                    <div class=\"update-date\">2026-03-06</div>\n   491→                    <div class=\"update-link\"><a href=\"https://github.blog/changelog/2026-03-06-github-copilot-in-visual-studio-code-v1-110-february-release/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">View Changelog →</a></div>\n   492→                    <div class=\"quote\">\"Makes agents practical for longer-running tasks\"</div>\n   493→                </div>\n   494→\n   495→                <div class=\"update-item\">\n   496→                    <div class=\"update-product\">Codex CLI</div>\n   497→                    <div class=\"update-title\">Version 0.110.0 - Plugin System</div>\n   498→                    <div class=\"update-description\">Plugin system to load skills and MCP entries, plus multi-agent TUI improvements.</div>\n   499→                    <div class=\"update-date\">2026-03-05</div>\n   500→                    <div class=\"update-link\"><a href=\"https://developers.openai.com/codex/changelog/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">View Changelog →</a></div>\n   501→                </div>\n   502→\n   503→                <div class=\"update-item\">\n   504→                    <div class=\"update-product\">Cursor</div>\n   505→                    <div class=\"update-title\">Automations - Always-On Agents Framework</div>\n   506→                    <div class=\"update-description\">Always-on agents triggered by Slack, Linear, GitHub, PagerDuty, webhooks. Access to MCPs and memory tools. <span class=\"highlight\">2x more agent users than Tab users</span>.</div>\n   507→                    <div class=\"update-date\">2026-03-05</div>\n   508→                    <div class=\"update-link\"><a href=\"https://cursor.com/automations\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">View Changelog →</a></div>\n   509→                </div>\n   510→\n   511→                <div class=\"update-item\">\n   512→                    <div class=\"update-product\">Cursor</div>\n   513→                    <div class=\"update-title\">Cursor in JetBrains IDEs</div>\n   514→                    <div class=\"update-description\">Now available in IntelliJ IDEA, PyCharm, WebStorm via Agent Client Protocol (ACP). Frontier models from OpenAI, Anthropic, Google, Cursor.</div>\n   515→                    <div class=\"update-date\">2026-03-04</div>\n   516→                    <div class=\"update-link\"><a href=\"https://cursor.com/changelog\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">View Changelog →</a></div>\n   517→                </div>\n   518→\n   519→                <div class=\"update-item\">\n   520→                    <div class=\"update-product\">Devin</div>\n   521→                    <div class=\"update-title\">Install Devin as an App (PWA)</div>\n   522→                    <div class=\"update-description\">Progressive Web App for desktop and mobile. Install from Chrome/Edge. Includes bug fixes, performance improvements, visual polish.</div>\n   523→                    <div class=\"update-date\">2026-03-07</div>\n   524→                    <div class=\"update-link\"><a href=\"https://docs.devin.ai/release-notes/overview\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">View Changelog →</a></div>\n   525→                    <div class=\"quote\">\"Where did Devin go? What does it say about the future?\"</div>\n   526→                </div>\n   527→\n   528→                <div class=\"update-item\">\n   529→                    <div class=\"update-product\">Gemini CLI</div>\n   530→                    <div class=\"update-title\">v0.32.0 - Generalist Agent & Model Steering</div>\n   531→                    <div class=\"update-description\">Generalist agent enabled for better task delegation. New model steering within workspace environments.</div>\n   532→                    <div class=\"update-date\">2026-03-03</div>\n   533→                    <div class=\"update-link\"><a href=\"https://geminicli.com/docs/changelogs/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">View Changelog →</a></div>\n   534→                </div>\n   535→            </section>\n   536→\n   537→            <!-- Technical Insights Section -->\n   538→            <section id=\"technical-insights\">\n   539→                <h2>Technical Insights (7)</h2>\n   540→\n   541→                <div class=\"insight-item\">\n   542→                    <div class=\"insight-title\">AI-assisted coding is exposing a divide among developers</div>\n   543→                    <div class=\"insight-author\">Simon Willison (citing Les Orchard)</div>\n   544→                    <div class=\"insight-summary\">AI reveals fundamental split between 'craft-lovers' and 'make-it-go' developers. Fork: let machines write code or hand-craft. Motivation becomes visible through choices.</div>\n   545→                    <div class=\"insight-meta\">\n   546→                        <span class=\"tag\">developer psychology</span>\n   547→                        <span class=\"tag\">Blog</span>\n   548→                        <span class=\"tag\">2026-03-12</span>\n   549→                    </div>\n   550→                </div>\n   551→\n   552→                <div class=\"insight-item\">\n   553→                    <div class=\"insight-title\">Coding After Coders: The End of Computer Programming as We Know It</div>\n   554→                    <div class=\"insight-author\">Clive Thompson (NYT Magazine)</div>\n   555→                    <div class=\"insight-summary\">Features 70+ developers from Google, Amazon, Microsoft, Apple. Simon: \"Tether AI to reality by testing if code runs correctly.\" Discusses Jevons paradox potentially increasing demand.</div>\n   556→                    <div class=\"insight-meta\">\n   557→                        <span class=\"tag\">industry transformation</span>\n   558→                        <span class=\"tag\">NYT Magazine</span>\n   559→                        <span class=\"tag\">2026-03-12</span>\n   560→                    </div>\n   561→                </div>\n   562→\n   563→                <div class=\"insight-item\">\n   564→                    <div class=\"insight-title\">MALUS—Clean Room as a Service</div>\n   565→                    <div class=\"insight-author\">Simon Willison</div>\n   566→                    <div class=\"insight-summary\">Satire on vibe-porting license washing: \"Proprietary AI robots recreate open source projects. Legally distinct code with corporate-friendly licensing.\" Willison: \"Too on-the-nose.\"</div>\n   567→                    <div class=\"insight-meta\">\n   568→                        <span class=\"tag\">open source licensing</span>\n   569→                        <span class=\"tag\">satire</span>\n   570→                        <span class=\"tag\">2026-03-12</span>\n   571→                    </div>\n   572→                </div>\n   573→\n   574→                <div class=\"insight-item\">\n   575→                    <div class=\"insight-title\">Meet The $9 Billion AI Company Reimagining Vibe Coding</div>\n   576→                    <div class=\"insight-author\">Richard Nieva (Forbes)</div>\n   577→                    <div class=\"insight-summary\">Replit raised $400M at $9B valuation (up from $3B in 6 months). Agent 4: digital canvas for vibe coding. Customers: Zillow (600 seats, 7,000+ apps), Databricks, PayPal, Adobe. Competes with Claude Code ($2.5B) and Cursor ($2B+).</div>\n   578→                    <div class=\"insight-meta\">\n   579→                        <span class=\"tag\">vibe coding</span>\n   580→                        <span class=\"tag\">startup funding</span>\n   581→                        <span class=\"tag\">2026-03-11</span>\n   582→                    </div>\n   583→                </div>\n   584→\n   585→                <div class=\"insight-item\">\n   586→                    <div class=\"insight-title\">AI should help us produce better code</div>\n   587→                    <div class=\"insight-author\">Simon Willison</div>\n   588→                    <div class=\"insight-summary\">Shipping worse code with agents is a choice - we can ship better code instead. Identify which process aspects hurt quality and fix them when adopting coding agents.</div>\n   589→                    <div class=\"insight-meta\">\n   590→                        <span class=\"tag\">code quality</span>\n   591→                        <span class=\"tag\">opinion</span>\n   592→                        <span class=\"tag\">2026-03-10</span>\n   593→                    </div>\n   594→                </div>\n   595→\n   596→                <div class=\"insight-item\">\n   597→                    <div class=\"insight-title\">Perhaps not Boring Technology after all</div>\n   598→                    <div class=\"insight-author\">Simon Willison</div>\n   599→                    <div class=\"insight-summary\">Latest models in good coding agent harnesses show excellent results even with brand new or private tools. Agents consume docs and learn from codebases. Discusses Skills mechanism from Remotion, Supabase, Vercel, Prisma.</div>\n   600→                    <div class=\"insight-meta\">\n   601→                        <span class=\"tag\">LLM technology choices</span>\n   602→                        <span class=\"tag\">skills mechanism</span>\n   603→                        <span class=\"tag\">2026-03-09</span>\n   604→                    </div>\n   605→                </div>\n   606→\n   607→                <div class=\"insight-item\">\n   608→                    <div class=\"insight-title\">Organizational Context for AI Coding Agents</div>\n   609→                    <div class=\"insight-author\">Dennis Pilarinos (Unblocked CEO)</div>\n   610→                    <div class=\"insight-summary\">Podcast: Context challenge - why systems work, architectural decisions, sources of truth. Unblocked aggregates knowledge from code, PRs, docs, chat, telemetry. Context engineering, permission systems, shifting bottlenecks.</div>\n   611→                    <div class=\"insight-meta\">\n   612→                        <span class=\"tag\">organizational context</span>\n   613→                        <span class=\"tag\">Podcast</span>\n   614→                        <span class=\"tag\">2026-03-05</span>\n   615→                    </div>\n   616→                </div>\n   617→            </section>\n   618→        </main>\n   619→\n   620→        <footer>\n   621→            <p>Generated by <a href=\"https://agentdaily.com\">Agent Code Daily</a> - Powered by <a href=\"https://claude.com/claude-code\">Claude Agent SDK</a></p>\n   622→            <p style=\"margin-top: 5px;\">Report compiled from Product Hunt, Hacker News, Reddit, and technical blogs • Last updated: March 13, 2026</p>\n   623→        </footer>\n   624→    </div>\n   625→</body>\n   626→</html>"
      }
    ]
